ra2,"2. How We Collect Information
A. Information You Provide

We may collect Personal Information you provide to us:

When you fill out forms or fields through our Services;
When you sign up for any newsletters or other materials through our Services;
When you provide information to us through a Third-Party application, service or web site;
When you communicate with us or request information about us or our Services, whether via email or other means;
When you participate in online surveys hosted by us or our Third-Party partners;
When you participate in any of our marketing initiatives, including, contests, sweepstakes, or other promotions;
When you participate in forums, chats or provide user generated content or submissions;
When you provide us with access to GPS-based information about your location; and
When you visit our Sites or open emails we send, including your device identifier or IP address.",Categories of Personal Information Collected

ra2,"3. How We Use Your Information
A. Internal Uses

In addition to the uses described in the Information We Collect section of this Privacy Policy, we may use each category of your Personal Information for business purposes such as:

to provide you the Services you request (such as promotions, lending and scholarship information);
to operate, administer, test and improve our Sites;
to customize our Sites, including with location-based information, advertising, and features;
to improve your user experience and our Services;
to provide information about other products and services which we think might interest you;
to provide you with and target advertising based on your activity and interests, both on our own Sites and applications and on third-party sites, platforms and applications; and
for our general business purposes such as analytics, market research and financial reporting.
We use Sensitive Personal Information as described above and we use and/or disclose it for additional purposes beyond those specified in 11 Cal. Code of Regs. § 7027(m). For information about how to opt-out of our processing of Sensitive Personal Information for non-exempt purposes, please see the Consumer Privacy Rights section below.

B. Consumer Rewards Services

We also use each category of your Personal Information for purposes of establishing and maintaining our consumer rewards services, such as RewardFish. Rewards opportunities may include cashback shopping, offers, surveys, search, watching video and other online and offline activities. You should review our Notice of Financial Incentive related to the rewards opportunities.

C. Personal Information Disclosures

We may disclose your Personal Information for the purposes in this Privacy Policy to:

Service Providers: From time to time, we may use other businesses to perform specific services (“Service Providers”), such as sending emails or newsletters to Edvisors users. We may disclose your Personal Information to the extent necessary for the Service Provider to provide specific services including, but not limited to:

Fulfillment and account servicing vendors, which help us provide products, services and information to you, service your account or benefits, and perform payment processing services;
Marketing and communications vendors, which help us market our products/services to you, conduct promotions, surveys and other outreach campaigns, and facilitate communications via phone, text, email, and chat;
Research and development vendors, which help us develop and improve our products and services;
Data and business analytics vendors, which help us collect, analyze and improve the accuracy of our data (including Personal Information);
IT and network administration vendors, which provide services such as data storage and management, website hosting, and data security;
Professional service firms, which provide accounting, legal, and other professional services; and
General service providers, which help us with day-to-day business operations such as office support services, courier services, facilities management, and document destruction.
These Service Providers may be located outside of your home jurisdiction. Our Service Providers are only allowed to use Personal Information for the purpose of providing the specific services requested by Edvisors. The services covered by this paragraph do not include links to third-party sites found on our sites.

We may also disclose your Personal Information to Third Parties for the following purposes when permitted or required by applicable law:

Law Enforcement: While Edvisors strives to protect the Personal Information of all users, Edvisors will disclose Personal Information if legally required to do so, if requested to do so by a government entity, or if it believes in good faith that such action is necessary to: (a) conform to legal requirements or comply with legal process; (b) protect our rights or property or our affiliated companies; (c) prevent a crime or protect national security; or (d) protect the personal safety of users or the public.

As Part of a Business Transfer: We may disclose your Personal Information, including usage information with any parent, subsidiary or affiliate entity for the purposes disclosed in this Privacy Policy. We also reserve the right to disclose and transfer some or all such information: (i) to a subsequent owner, co-owner or operator of Edvisors; or (ii) in connection with any merger, acquisition, consolidation, restructuring, bankruptcy, sale of assets or other corporate change involving us and/or our affiliates. We may transfer the corresponding information regarding our customers and users of the Services, including Personal Information, to Third Parties evaluating or facilitating the transaction.

Nothing in this Privacy Policy is intended to interfere with our ability to transfer all or part of our business, equity interests, or assets (including the Services) to an affiliate or non-affiliated third party at any time, for any purpose, without any limitation, and without notice or any compensation to you.

Consent: In addition to the other disclosure practices described in this Privacy Policy, we may also disclose your Personal Information to Third Parties with your consent.",Categories of Personal Information Sold

